\n<Roselitte>"I'm fine. The doctor told me to rest, but I actually feel
quite good."

\n<Lyric>"You're exaggerating, she's totally fine. Despite looking
like she was on death's door, she's bouncing back already."

\n<Lyric>"No, I will say it. I'll say it until I die. You emotional
scam artist."

\n<Lyric>"Remember when Ameria 'collapsed just like this' and got
right back up to treat others? And here you are, cozying up
in a nice room like this."

\n<Lyric>"What's with this 'I want you by my side' nonsense. Since
when did you become so frail, Roselitte-chan?"

\n<Ameria>"Eh~? My throat's been parched since then, it's been tough,
you know?"
\n<Roselitte>"...Both of you, you can go home now."
\n<Lyric>"As if you want us to leave. Right, Ameria?♪"
\n<Ameria>"Even preparing such chairs for us. Right, Lyric?♪"
\n<Roselitte>"...Ah, my head is starting to hurt..."
Roselitte and the others continued to chat for a while.

\n<Roselitte>"--So, are you going to proceed as planned and head to the
mainland of Valam?"

\n<Ameria>"Yes. The injured people in town should be fine without me
now, and there are priests on the mainland.... I can't stay
here anymore."
\n<Ameria>"...Roselitte-san, I still feel like I owe everyone..."
\n<Roselitte>"No. If you want to atone, keep that feeling in your heart."
\n<Roselitte>"...Besides, first you should talk to this person."
Roselitte took out an envelope from her bosom.
\n<Roselitte>"Please hand over this letter when you meet the priest."

\n<Roselitte>"...I sent a soldier to the mainland the other day. I've
ordered them to release the priest from prison and treat him
with the utmost respect."

\n<Roselitte>"Yes. And I've arranged for them to wait for your arrival.
You'll need some rest too, and it would be troublesome if
there was a mix-up."

\n<Roselitte>"You don't need to thank me. Ideally, I should accompany you
and speak directly, but as you can see, I'm not in a state
to do so. Please deliver the letter on my behalf."
\n<Ameria>"The doctor said you still can't go outside?"
\n<Roselitte>"Just a few more days of rest is what they said."

\n<Ameria>"That's a shame we can't go together, but if that's the
case, it can't be helped."
\n<Roselitte>"Yes. The injured must listen to their doctors."
\n<Roselitte>"Lyric, make sure not to take your eyes off Ameria."
\n<Lyric>"Ah, come on, don't cling to me, it's annoying!"

\n<Lyric>"...sigh. There's no need to worry about me. You should take
it easy for a change."

\n<Roselitte>"Indeed... Somehow, I've gotten into the habit of worrying
about you two."
\n<Lyric>"Haha. You're more of a guardian than anyone else."
\n<Lyric>"--Oh, that reminds me. Before I forget..."
Lyric placed the journal on the bed.
\n<Lyric>"...You don't mind if I leave this with you, right?"

\n<Roselitte>"Yes. It's too dangerous for you two to carry it around.
Leave the investigation of the book to me."
Lyric nodded and placed her hand on her chest.
\n<Roselitte>"Do as you like. That will surely be the right decision."
\n<Ameria>"...Ah, it's already this late. We should be leaving soon."
\n<Lyric>"If you're lonely, shall I stay a bit longer?"

\n<Ameria>"Then... thank you for letting us rest here, Roselitte-san.
Take care and rest well."
\n<Roselitte>"...I've decided to quit being a knight."

\n<Roselitte>"Ah... It doesn't mean I'm retiring. Even if I quit being a
knight, I won't abandon my sword."

\n<Roselitte>"This life that I've nearly lost twice, I want to use it not
for the Empire, but for myself and for you all."

\n<Roselitte>"...Ever since I became aware, I've dedicated my life to the
Empire and walked the path of a knight. I believed that was
the right path for me."

\n<Roselitte>"...That's why I've been troubled ever since I got injured.
If I can't fight for the Empire, then I'm worthless. There's
nothing left for me. How should I accept myself from now
on...?"

\n<Roselitte>"...But after meeting you all and traveling together, I've
found a new path."

\n<Roselitte>"I want to wield my sword for the sake of those who are
precious to me."

\n<Roselitte>"From now on, not as a knight but as a woman with a sword,
as 'Roselitte Hausen', I want to walk a new path."
Roselitte extended both her hands towards them.

\n<Roselitte>"I want to use this power for my new self and for the two of
you who gave me a future."

\n<Roselitte>"If you two are ever in trouble, I will definitely help you.
If there are enemies standing in your way, I will defeat
them... anytime, no matter who they are."
\n<Roselitte>"...Will you continue to be my friends from now on?"
Ameria gripped one of her hands back.

\n<Ameria>"Yes. I will also always be there to help you, Roselitte-
san."

\n<Ameria>"...And I will definitely heal that injury. I'll study a lot
more, gain more power... and I'm sure, I'll heal it."
Roselitte and Ameria smiled at each other.
While saying that, Lyric gripped Roselitte's hand.
Roselitte embraced their hands as if praying to God.

\n<Roselitte>"Princess Iris... What brings you to such a place?"

\n<Iris>"How could I just sit quietly on the mainland when my
brother has been taken hostage? It's good to see you're
safe."

\n<Iris>"I've heard the stories. Roselitte. Ameria. And... Lyric.
Thank you all for your efforts on behalf of our Empire. On
behalf of His Majesty, I would like to express our
gratitude."

\n<Iris>"I would love to hear all about it from the three of you.
Roselitte's battle experiences are always so thrilling.
There must have been quite the ordeal this time, right?"

\n<Roselitte>"...I apologize, Princess Iris. The two of them have urgent
matters to attend to shortly. If you wish to talk, I alone
can..."

\n<Iris>"Is that so... That's a shame. I haven't even properly
thanked you yet. Where are you rushing off to in such a
hurry?"
\n<Ameria>"To the mainland. There's someone waiting for us there."

\n<Iris>"Oh! Then that's perfect. I was planning to check on
Roselitte and the others before heading back to the mainland
myself. How about we go together?"

\n<Iris>"There's a carriage available and soldiers too, so it would
be faster and safer to travel to the mainland together...
What do you think? It's not a bad offer, right?"

\n<Iris>"...Roselitte, you should come too. It's a bit of a distance
and the carriage ride will be bumpy, but the mainland will
be better for your recovery, right? There are doctors there,
so there shouldn't be any problems on the way."
Ameria looked at Roselitte with a happy gaze.
\n<Roselitte>"...Yes. Thank you very much. I will accompany you as well."

\n<Iris>"Then... the two of you wait outside first. I'll tell the
soldiers to have the carriage ready."

\n<Lyric>"...No? It's just rare to see someone important from the
human world. I was wondering what kind of person they might
be."

\n<Iris>"Hehe. I'm just a human who happened to be born into
royalty."
\n<Iris>"Or do you see something special when you look at me?"

\n<Lyric>"That's right. I would definitely like to have a leisurely
chat with you sometime, princess."
\n<Iris>"Oh... To hear such words from your mouth."
Roselitte looked down at the magic book in her hands.

\n<Roselitte>"Just a journal.... Please wait a moment while I gather my
things."
\n<Iris>"Since when did you become a naughty child who lies to me?"

\n<Iris>"...Well, knowing you, you're not trying to deceive me. But
it doesn't feel good to have secrets kept from me right in
front of my eyes."
Iris reached out for the journal.

Iris gently stroked the cover of the journal she took in her
hand.

\n<Iris>"--Tch. That failure. Doing as they please without my
knowledge..."

\n<Iris>"...Ah, no need to worry. As you said, this is now just a
journal. Nothing strange should happen."

\n<Iris>"Besides, that child is mine. I can handle them however I
want."
\n<Roselitte>"...Is Iris-sama one of the magic book's companions?"
Iris gently brushed aside Roselitte's bangs.

\n<Iris>"Are you one of the child's... one of the magic book's
companions?"

\n<Roselitte>"Huh--? What are you talking about? There's no way that's
possible!"

\n<Iris>"...First off, why did you chase after your brother in such
a state?"
\n<Iris>"You weren't trying to interfere with me, were you?"

\n<Roselitte>"Lord Yuri went on an expedition without even taking the
royal guards with him, you know? How could I possibly leave
him be in such danger!"

\n<Iris>"...'Fate's encounter' is something unpredictable, isn't
it?"
\n<Iris>"Yes, that's right. I understand. You're a very good girl."

\n<Iris>"I'm sorry for suspecting you. I've become a little
hypersensitive to betrayal."

\n<Iris>"Yes, of course. I'll tell you everything. You're too
involved to be left out of the loop now."

The hand Iris had over her mouth and her pale lips were
smeared with dark red blood.
\n<Roselitte>"Are you... alright? Do you have your medicine...?"

\n<Roselitte>"Why wouldn't I be... You're bleeding. Do you have your
medicine with you?"

\n<Iris>"...Roselitte, I'm sorry. It was necessary. But I think
you'll understand."
\n<Iris>"To move a nation, one needs a just cause."

\n<Iris>"...I'm a bit tired. It's a long story, so let's talk about
it in detail another time."

\n<Iris>"...But we must hurry. First, I need you to take 'her'
place."

\n<Iris>"That woman, believe it or not, has betrayed me... no, she
has defied His Majesty's orders and betrayed us Valams."

\n<Iris>"She tried to kill you, the one I entrusted with 'that
operation'."
\n<Iris>"The one to take you to the mainland is none other than me."

\n<Iris>"Ameria Aurcus. Detain her and escort her to the mainland.
Do not take your eyes off her."

\n<Iris>"And as 'the replacement for the traitor,' you will fulfill
this mission."

\n<Iris>"...Roselitte Schwarz. I command you in the name of His
Imperial Majesty."
Iris took Roselitte's hand with her own blood-stained hand.

\n<Iris>"For someone like you, you're a bit slow, aren't you? Love
is blind. It's true that you can't see your surroundings.
I've never been in love with anyone, so I wouldn't
understand."

\n<Iris>"You were curious, weren't you? Despite it being to spread
the dignity of the next Emperor, why would someone of the
Crown Prince's stature need to personally deal with mere
bandits?"

\n<Iris>"The answer is simple. To bring you here. A suitable reason
was needed to pull you out of the infirmary while you were
injured, right?"
\n<Roselitte>"...Such... No way! Even the bandits attacking the village!"

\n<Iris>"It's fortunate this is a remote land. Even if bandits or
monsters run wild, the number of people affected is
limited... I was really nervous when they almost crossed the
national border though."
\n<Roselitte>"You knew as well, Lady Iris!? Did your brother know?"

\n<Iris>"My brother? Of course not. There's no way such a simpleton
with nothing but a sense of justice would know."
\n<Iris>"That person was just bait to bring you here... And then--"
Iris took out "Roselitte's Journal" from her bosom.
\n<Roselitte>"That is... I lost it in the cave..."

\n<Iris>"Ameria would surely lend you the book. Lyric would surely
arouse your lust. You would surely do whatever it takes to
save your brother... That's what I believed."
Roselitte clutched her head and scratched at it.

\n<Roselitte>"--I am! What have I been fighting for...! For what purpose
have I been battling...!!"

\n<Iris>"Fate's encounters are unpredictable... But there's one
thing I want you to understand."
Iris gently brushed aside Roselitte's bangs.

\n<Iris>"I also wanted to heal your injuries. I was truly shocked
when you got hurt during 'that operation'."

\n<Iris>"...Don't be so distressed, Roselitte. All of this was done
for the Empire. And for you, who are so precious."

Having said that, Iris caressed the grimoire she held in her
hand.

\n<Iris>"I told it to inform me once it found the succubus's
location, but this child tried to awaken Begierde on its
own. Despite being just a copy, it plotted to become the
true Begierde."

\n<Iris>"...And in the end, it failed and even killed the succubus
'before awakening.' Such a failure. Trash. Rubbish. Don't
you think so too?"

\n<Iris>"...But fate's encounters are unpredictable. Just when I was
about to dispose of this child, news came that you were
gravely injured during 'that operation.'

\n<Iris>"Not only that. The succubus we thought dead was alive, and
it became clear that your injury might be the key to
awakening Begierde."
Iris gently brushed aside Roselitte's bangs.

\n<Iris>"...I also wanted to heal your injuries. In this world full
of incompetents. You, a woman who is strong and a loyal
knight, are one of the few humans I respect."
\n<Iris>"...So, I decided to give the grimoire one last chance."

\n<Iris>"If your injury could be healed by the power of desire. If
Begierde could be awakened under my watchful eye. Then I
promised not to dispose of it as a reward."

\n<Iris>"In the end, the key was a red herring, and the grimoire
tried to kill you. Even though your injuries have improved
slightly, I can't forgive it."
Iris placed her hand on her chest.
\n<Iris>"I intended to do this from the beginning."
\n<Iris>"I won't tell a liar like you."

\n<Iris>"...But if you're willing to take 'her' place, I might just
tell you."

\n<Iris>"Yes. 'That woman' dared to defy not just me but... no, His
Majesty's orders, and betrayed us Valam by trying to kill
you—the one I entrusted with that operation."

\n<Iris>"Escort Ameria back to the mainland. Don't take your eyes
off her... and fulfill the role of 'that woman.'

\n<Iris>"...Roselitte Schwarz. I command you in the name of His
Imperial Majesty."
